1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:40,000
( Watch on www.kissasia.co, .club, .be, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

2
00:00:49,404 --> 00:00:52,073
STILL SHINING

3
00:01:11,676 --> 00:01:13,136
ACCESS

4
00:01:13,720 --> 00:01:15,930
The changing room
is down the hall on the right.

5
00:01:16,014 --> 00:01:17,724
You can put on a uniform in your size.

6
00:01:18,433 --> 00:01:20,226
Did you bring a pair of black flats?

7
00:01:20,310 --> 00:01:21,311
Yes.

8
00:01:22,103 --> 00:01:23,104
You may go in.

9
00:01:26,608 --> 00:01:28,234
CHANGING ROOM

10
00:01:28,776 --> 00:01:30,194
Work starts at 2:00 p.m.

11
00:01:30,278 --> 00:01:32,322
So we'll move at 1:55 p.m.

12
00:01:32,405 --> 00:01:33,406
-Yes, ma'am.
-Yes, ma'am.

13
00:01:42,206 --> 00:01:43,791
Could you try these on?

14
00:01:43,875 --> 00:01:44,876
Okay.

15
00:02:07,357 --> 00:02:14,322
STILL SHINING

16
00:02:28,169 --> 00:02:29,671
When are the guests leaving?

17
00:02:31,005 --> 00:02:32,006
In 30 or 40 minutes.

18
00:02:33,258 --> 00:02:34,676
How was the work?

19
00:02:36,219 --> 00:02:37,220
It was hard,

20
00:02:37,303 --> 00:02:38,596
but it was fun.

21
00:02:42,308 --> 00:02:43,351
Geez, I'm tired.

22
00:02:49,565 --> 00:02:51,985
So this is what it looks like from here.

23
00:02:52,068 --> 00:02:54,612
I can see the mountains.

24
00:02:54,696 --> 00:02:56,447
And the sunset too.

25
00:02:58,449 --> 00:03:02,954
I'll work part-time on weekends for now.
Then, I'll decide to take time off or not.

26
00:03:03,997 --> 00:03:05,665
You should once you're an intern.

27
00:03:06,332 --> 00:03:07,709
Apply for the summer internship.

28
00:03:10,920 --> 00:03:14,632
When you become an intern,
you can move into the residence hall.

29
00:03:16,467 --> 00:03:17,468
What's that?

30
00:03:17,552 --> 00:03:18,386
The dorms.

31
00:03:19,804 --> 00:03:20,805
The dorms?

32
00:03:22,890 --> 00:03:25,226
You can dorm once you become an intern.

33
00:03:25,309 --> 00:03:27,395
How long is the internship?

34
00:03:27,478 --> 00:03:28,980
It depends.

35
00:03:29,063 --> 00:03:32,358
It can be for summer vacation,
for half a year, or for even a year.

36
00:03:33,317 --> 00:03:35,111
If they're providing housing in dorms,

37
00:03:36,279 --> 00:03:38,990
the internship must be long and tough.

38
00:03:39,657 --> 00:03:41,159
I might take a break from school.

39
00:03:42,035 --> 00:03:43,494
Have you selected a department yet?

40
00:03:44,537 --> 00:03:45,455
Not yet.

41
00:03:46,039 --> 00:03:47,832
Should I take
the first position that opens?

42
00:03:48,583 --> 00:03:49,417
If possible,

43
00:03:50,460 --> 00:03:52,462
I hope you get the position you want.

44
00:03:53,254 --> 00:03:54,255
The position I want?

45
00:03:58,009 --> 00:03:59,844
I'll ask what departments they have.

46
00:04:00,970 --> 00:04:02,638
I'm happy just thinking about it.

47
00:04:07,101 --> 00:04:08,770
You're good at English,

48
00:04:08,853 --> 00:04:10,813
you like people,

49
00:04:10,897 --> 00:04:12,565
and you draw vegetables well.

50
00:04:12,648 --> 00:04:14,150
I told you there was a job for you.

51
00:04:14,859 --> 00:04:17,904
Geez. I can't believe you remember that.

52
00:04:24,869 --> 00:04:28,122
Vegetable drawings
are probably going to be useless.

53
00:04:29,707 --> 00:04:31,793
I hope it's somewhere I can speak English.

54
00:04:31,876 --> 00:04:33,669
I'm good at casual small talk.

55
00:04:33,753 --> 00:04:36,172
Before So-hyeon was around,
I used to talk with guests

56
00:04:36,255 --> 00:04:38,216
when there weren't too many of them.

57
00:04:38,299 --> 00:04:40,551
I can speak English with confidence.
Impressive, right?

58
00:04:41,803 --> 00:04:42,678
You're all excited.

59
00:04:44,055 --> 00:04:44,889
I am.

60
00:04:46,182 --> 00:04:48,434
My dream of becoming independent
felt uncertain,

61
00:04:48,518 --> 00:04:50,269
but it's feeling more concrete now.

62
00:04:51,270 --> 00:04:52,855
I guess this is what opportunity is.

63
00:05:02,949 --> 00:05:06,202
I only work on weekends for now,
but I'll gradually start working weekdays.

64
00:05:07,203 --> 00:05:08,704
I'm free only on the weekends though.

65
00:05:09,497 --> 00:05:12,542
-Matching our schedules might be…
-How about Friday nights?

66
00:05:14,085 --> 00:05:16,462
-Let's work it out.
-Yeah.

67
00:05:18,464 --> 00:05:21,259
When it's destiny, it's not vague.

68
00:05:21,342 --> 00:05:23,511
It's clear. You don't hesitate about it.

69
00:05:24,595 --> 00:05:28,266
I guess that's how people find
direction in life and move forward.

70
00:05:29,350 --> 00:05:32,270
I'm curious. In what way is it clear?

71
00:05:33,187 --> 00:05:34,564
You can feel it.

72
00:05:34,647 --> 00:05:37,692
Because of you,
I know what destiny feels like.

73
00:05:40,027 --> 00:05:41,654
Why don't I know it then?

74
00:05:43,281 --> 00:05:45,199
As soon as you see something, bam, boom!

75
00:05:45,283 --> 00:05:48,411
It feels strong and clear.
Try to think back.

76
00:05:50,496 --> 00:05:51,581
Bam? Boom?

77
00:05:52,748 --> 00:05:54,041
I've felt that so many times.

78
00:05:54,792 --> 00:05:56,002
When did you feel it?

79
00:06:00,006 --> 00:06:01,841
What? When was it?

80
00:06:03,551 --> 00:06:07,346
When you stumbled
as if you were about to faint

81
00:06:07,430 --> 00:06:09,140
while walking across the schoolyard.

82
00:06:09,807 --> 00:06:12,602
Me? Come on. I've never stumbled.

83
00:06:13,311 --> 00:06:15,271
Sorry. Was that too strong?

84
00:06:16,189 --> 00:06:17,231
Hey!

85
00:06:18,024 --> 00:06:20,943
I guess you're okay with me
going home alone now?

86
00:06:21,944 --> 00:06:22,945
Does it upset you?

87
00:06:24,697 --> 00:06:25,698
A little.

88
00:06:27,033 --> 00:06:28,159
Nice job adapting.

89
00:06:48,346 --> 00:06:49,555
I'll come down Saturday night.

90
00:06:51,974 --> 00:06:55,603
If I leave right after tutoring,
it'll be around 11:00 p.m. And…

91
00:06:57,521 --> 00:06:59,523
I've never felt comfortable

92
00:06:59,607 --> 00:07:01,317
seeing you leave alone.

93
00:07:02,318 --> 00:07:03,319
Okay?

94
00:07:13,829 --> 00:07:16,165
"I hope you enjoy your time here."

95
00:07:19,126 --> 00:07:22,463
"I hope you enjoy your time here."
Your time here?

96
00:07:24,674 --> 00:07:25,675
"Your time here."

97
00:07:26,384 --> 00:07:27,885
We'll head out onto the floor.

98
00:07:27,969 --> 00:07:29,178
-Yes, ma'am.
-Yes, ma'am.

99
00:07:42,358 --> 00:07:43,609
The guests are still here.

100
00:07:44,360 --> 00:07:45,820
Okay. Have a good one.

101
00:07:48,864 --> 00:07:50,950
SAINT OCEAN HOTEL
SUMMER INTERNSHIP PROGRAM

102
00:07:51,033 --> 00:07:53,452
INTERNSHIP BENEFITS
FREE DORMITORY ACCOMMODATION

103
00:08:04,839 --> 00:08:06,841
I'm so exhausted.

104
00:08:10,177 --> 00:08:12,346
But it's so much fun.

105
00:08:16,892 --> 00:08:17,727
Tae-seo.

106
00:08:50,176 --> 00:08:51,177
How's the food?

107
00:08:51,260 --> 00:08:54,013
-It's so well-arranged and delicious.
-Thank you.

108
00:08:54,096 --> 00:08:55,181
Is there anything you need?

109
00:08:55,264 --> 00:08:56,515
Gosh, there's so much food.

110
00:08:56,599 --> 00:08:58,809
-We'll let you know.
-Thanks for the food.

111
00:08:58,893 --> 00:09:00,019
Let's try them in order.

112
00:09:15,618 --> 00:09:16,911
I'm coming in.

113
00:09:46,857 --> 00:09:49,318
I think Eun-a's exhausted.

114
00:09:50,069 --> 00:09:51,529
The work must be hard.

115
00:09:52,279 --> 00:09:53,280
I don't know.

116
00:09:53,906 --> 00:09:54,865
Ask her yourself.

117
00:09:56,325 --> 00:09:57,702
She won't tell me.

118
00:09:58,869 --> 00:10:01,080
This was cooked really nicely.

119
00:10:01,163 --> 00:10:02,915
Could you take some to her
before it's gone?

120
00:10:02,998 --> 00:10:04,875
Wait. Will she hate it
because it's fattening?

121
00:10:06,502 --> 00:10:08,963
They're asking for me.
You should take it to her yourself.

122
00:10:09,672 --> 00:10:10,756
She won't eat it if I do.

123
00:10:10,840 --> 00:10:12,007
Don't be intimidated by her.

124
00:10:13,134 --> 00:10:15,886
Check in on her and ask her everything.

125
00:10:23,436 --> 00:10:24,478
Hold still.

126
00:10:24,562 --> 00:10:26,355
-What?
-Is that it?

127
00:10:30,317 --> 00:10:31,152
Eun-a.

128
00:10:32,111 --> 00:10:33,195
Eun-a!

129
00:10:42,163 --> 00:10:44,957
Why were you hiding your relationship?

130
00:10:46,083 --> 00:10:49,044
We started seeing each other
during senior year,

131
00:10:49,128 --> 00:10:51,130
so we didn't want our families to worry.

132
00:10:51,756 --> 00:10:55,426
There's no need to hide it anymore,
but I guess we got used to it.

133
00:10:56,218 --> 00:10:57,678
We won't do that anymore.

134
00:10:57,762 --> 00:10:59,096
We're fine on our own.

135
00:10:59,180 --> 00:11:01,056
Can you just come down and talk to us?

136
00:11:04,977 --> 00:11:06,437
I understand.

137
00:11:07,104 --> 00:11:09,273
It's a small town,
so they'd just gossip about it.

138
00:11:09,899 --> 00:11:10,900
That's right.

139
00:11:12,568 --> 00:11:14,987
Okay, let's keep it a secret.
I'll stay quiet too.

140
00:11:17,031 --> 00:11:18,699
You're using contraception, right?

141
00:11:20,826 --> 00:11:22,661
We haven't done…

142
00:11:24,497 --> 00:11:26,081
Well, be careful in the future.

143
00:11:26,165 --> 00:11:29,335
Don't try to act like my mom, So-hyeon.

144
00:11:29,418 --> 00:11:30,586
Did I say something wrong?

145
00:11:31,253 --> 00:11:34,173
You're 20 years old now.
You're not young anymore.

146
00:11:34,757 --> 00:11:36,425
You should be careful about these things.

147
00:12:03,869 --> 00:12:04,870
So damn embarrassing.

148
00:12:17,675 --> 00:12:18,801
You're something else.

149
00:12:18,884 --> 00:12:22,763
You don't even pry or tell me what to do.

150
00:12:24,098 --> 00:12:26,433
How can I tell you what to do?

151
00:12:27,268 --> 00:12:29,770
All I can do is wait
until you feel better.

152
00:12:38,988 --> 00:12:40,447
She's going to marry my dad.

153
00:12:41,574 --> 00:12:43,117
I like that my dad's getting married.

154
00:12:44,410 --> 00:12:46,579
But I don't know
what kind of person she is.

155
00:12:47,871 --> 00:12:51,083
She says she was born in Hawaii,
but she speaks fluent Korean.

156
00:12:51,166 --> 00:12:52,626
Sometimes, I think she's a scammer.

157
00:12:54,295 --> 00:12:56,630
But she goes harvesting
vegetables with Dad

158
00:12:56,714 --> 00:12:58,132
and gladly does all the hard work.

159
00:12:59,216 --> 00:13:02,094
One moment, I feel like it's good
that Dad has someone like her.

160
00:13:02,845 --> 00:13:04,096
Then the next moment, I don't.

161
00:13:06,307 --> 00:13:07,308
Anyway,

162
00:13:07,391 --> 00:13:08,726
I feel uneasy at home.

163
00:13:09,643 --> 00:13:11,228
I should hurry and move out.

164
00:13:14,231 --> 00:13:15,941
Does that answer all the questions

165
00:13:17,026 --> 00:13:18,193
in your head?

166
00:13:22,698 --> 00:13:23,699
It's just…

167
00:13:24,617 --> 00:13:27,161
I only want to tell you
about nice and happy things.

168
00:13:28,037 --> 00:13:29,496
I try not to talk about my problems.

169
00:13:30,456 --> 00:13:32,708
Do I seem like
I'm still having a hard time?

170
00:13:34,752 --> 00:13:35,961
No.

171
00:13:37,671 --> 00:13:38,714
But I don't know.

172
00:13:40,299 --> 00:13:42,718
I end up telling you everything anyway.

173
00:13:44,345 --> 00:13:45,346
Eun-a,

174
00:13:48,265 --> 00:13:49,308
I'm all right.

175
00:13:51,852 --> 00:13:55,356
You can tell me right away
when things are tough.

176
00:13:57,274 --> 00:14:00,235
Tell me when you feel lost, not after.

177
00:14:00,944 --> 00:14:02,988
Tell me even if I might not have
the right answer.

178
00:14:06,825 --> 00:14:07,826
I'll do that.

179
00:14:16,126 --> 00:14:17,544
Look at me, Eun-a.

180
00:14:18,796 --> 00:14:21,757
You said you felt at ease
when you looked at me.

181
00:14:21,840 --> 00:14:22,883
Look.

182
00:15:07,594 --> 00:15:14,560
JUNE

183
00:15:16,520 --> 00:15:19,606
I started writing my paper,
but it's still a draft.

184
00:15:19,690 --> 00:15:22,609
Since it's about AI controllers,
it's interesting.

185
00:15:23,235 --> 00:15:26,363
Which AI learning method are you using?

186
00:15:26,447 --> 00:15:28,032
The reinforcement learning method.

187
00:15:29,158 --> 00:15:31,368
I'm reading a paper about that.
Want me to look it up?

188
00:15:32,036 --> 00:15:33,078
That'd be great.

189
00:15:35,039 --> 00:15:36,707
Want to come to our lab during vacation?

190
00:15:37,291 --> 00:15:39,043
It's fun studying there during vacation.

191
00:15:40,377 --> 00:15:42,713
You might be able to become
a lab member too.

192
00:15:43,422 --> 00:15:44,715
You'll go to grad school anyway.

193
00:15:45,883 --> 00:15:48,177
-I haven't thought about it.
-Really?

194
00:15:48,260 --> 00:15:51,221
You're an academic type.
People like you end up in labs.

195
00:15:52,056 --> 00:15:53,390
What kind of person am I?

196
00:15:53,474 --> 00:15:54,767
You?

197
00:15:54,850 --> 00:15:56,727
You understand equations
in a physical sense.

198
00:15:56,810 --> 00:15:59,897
Those who try to grasp meanings
fixate on the nature of things.

199
00:16:00,481 --> 00:16:01,607
You should do what you like.

200
00:16:04,526 --> 00:16:08,322
Can liking something
be the basis for everything one does?

201
00:16:09,073 --> 00:16:11,075
Of course. What else would it be?

202
00:16:13,327 --> 00:16:16,955
One's condition, situation,
or responsibilities?

203
00:16:19,166 --> 00:16:20,334
That's refreshing to hear.

204
00:16:20,918 --> 00:16:22,836
No one decides their future
on those these days.

205
00:16:22,920 --> 00:16:24,213
They only focus on themselves.

206
00:16:25,422 --> 00:16:28,050
Anyway, come join us this summer.

207
00:16:30,511 --> 00:16:32,679
Hey, we don't let
just anyone join our lab.

208
00:16:32,763 --> 00:16:34,306
I know.

209
00:16:36,683 --> 00:16:38,352
Can I keep reading it?

210
00:16:38,435 --> 00:16:39,770
Of course. You're our ace.

211
00:16:40,729 --> 00:16:43,065
-I'm going to go see the professor.
-Okay. Thank you.

212
00:16:43,148 --> 00:16:43,982
Sure.

213
00:17:11,343 --> 00:17:13,220
What are you up to? Are you in class?

214
00:17:13,887 --> 00:17:15,848
I have a free period, so I'm in the lab.

215
00:17:16,473 --> 00:17:17,808
When should we meet?

216
00:17:18,600 --> 00:17:20,686
Let's match our schedules.
When's good for you?

217
00:17:24,523 --> 00:17:26,066
How about Wednesday evening?

218
00:17:26,817 --> 00:17:29,653
I have tutoring that I can't reschedule.
Exams are coming soon.

219
00:17:30,571 --> 00:17:33,615
I get off work at 7:00 p.m. on Friday.
I'm working Saturday afternoon.

220
00:17:34,950 --> 00:17:36,326
What about Saturday morning?

221
00:17:36,410 --> 00:17:40,247
SATURDAY
PREPARE FOR FINALS

222
00:17:41,707 --> 00:17:44,042
It works. I'll come to you.

223
00:17:51,508 --> 00:17:53,260
SEONG-CHAN

224
00:18:08,442 --> 00:18:09,276
Yes?

225
00:18:09,359 --> 00:18:10,611
Are you still at the hotel?

226
00:18:11,195 --> 00:18:13,197
The GRO team is looking for an intern.

227
00:18:13,947 --> 00:18:15,240
What's GRO?

228
00:18:16,158 --> 00:18:19,786
It's basically working the VIP lounge.
You might have the upper hand.

229
00:18:19,870 --> 00:18:22,497
The guests here often go to your place.

230
00:18:23,123 --> 00:18:25,000
This department might fit you well.

231
00:18:25,584 --> 00:18:26,710
It's perfect.

232
00:18:27,586 --> 00:18:29,129
I'm pretty familiar with my guests.

233
00:18:30,130 --> 00:18:31,548
That's why I'm recommending it.

234
00:18:31,632 --> 00:18:33,217
Go to the second floor.

235
00:18:33,300 --> 00:18:35,510
Introduce yourself
to the team leader, Yun Da-jeong.

236
00:18:35,594 --> 00:18:37,763
She'll know your place well.

237
00:18:37,846 --> 00:18:39,932
And tell her you're here
as a part-time worker.

238
00:18:43,518 --> 00:18:44,978
-Ms. Yun.
-Yes?

239
00:18:45,062 --> 00:18:47,314
-Guests are waiting downstairs.
-Okay. Thanks.

240
00:18:51,693 --> 00:18:53,820
Hello, ma'am. I'm Mo Eun-a.

241
00:18:53,904 --> 00:18:54,947
Right.

242
00:18:55,030 --> 00:18:56,698
Seong-chan told me about you.

243
00:18:57,449 --> 00:18:59,243
I'm working part-time at the banquet hall.

244
00:19:02,996 --> 00:19:05,082
I'll get going then.

245
00:19:05,832 --> 00:19:07,167
All right.

246
00:19:13,465 --> 00:19:16,009
Right. Are you free this Saturday morning?

247
00:19:16,093 --> 00:19:17,594
My team needs a part-timer.

248
00:19:17,678 --> 00:19:18,887
Yes, I'm free.

249
00:19:19,471 --> 00:19:20,472
See you then.

250
00:19:26,311 --> 00:19:27,354
Right, Tae-seo.

251
00:19:34,569 --> 00:19:35,737
Hello.

252
00:19:37,531 --> 00:19:38,824
Please come this way.

253
00:19:43,829 --> 00:19:45,122
Last time, we learned

254
00:19:45,205 --> 00:19:47,457
-about Fleming's Left-Hand Rule, right?
-Yes.

255
00:19:47,541 --> 00:19:48,709
This question's about that.

256
00:19:48,792 --> 00:19:50,377
The direction of rotation is plus…

257
00:19:50,460 --> 00:19:52,170
-Mr. Yeon.
-Yes?

258
00:19:53,338 --> 00:19:54,172
Just a second.

259
00:19:55,465 --> 00:19:56,800
Yes?

260
00:19:56,883 --> 00:19:58,677
Should I book you for Saturday morning?

261
00:20:00,137 --> 00:20:01,138
Well…

262
00:20:02,055 --> 00:20:03,724
I'm going home on Saturday.

263
00:20:04,808 --> 00:20:09,313
Mr. Yeon, their finals are almost here,
so weekends are a must for extra lessons.

264
00:20:12,274 --> 00:20:13,692
This is why we need real teachers.

265
00:20:15,027 --> 00:20:16,903
College students have no responsibility.

266
00:20:18,196 --> 00:20:19,197
What about Sunday?

267
00:20:22,784 --> 00:20:23,827
I can do it.

268
00:20:24,369 --> 00:20:25,829
What time should I put you down for?

269
00:20:27,372 --> 00:20:28,999
Around 1:00 p.m. or 2:00 p.m.

270
00:20:29,666 --> 00:20:31,168
I'll schedule you at 2:00 p.m. then.

271
00:20:32,502 --> 00:20:34,838
ROLLING STOCK DRIVER'S LICENSE

272
00:20:40,469 --> 00:20:41,845
What's that?

273
00:20:42,471 --> 00:20:44,681
Someone left it
and hasn't come to get it for months.

274
00:20:46,099 --> 00:20:49,436
When I cover cup noodles with this,
it provides the perfect pressure.

275
00:20:50,395 --> 00:20:53,482
Eat dinner at my place
before you go tutoring. It's nearby.

276
00:20:53,565 --> 00:20:55,233
My mom makes chicken soup every day.

277
00:20:55,317 --> 00:20:57,527
I'm sick of it. You eat it for me.

278
00:20:58,570 --> 00:21:00,822
I already ate. I need more sleep.

279
00:21:03,241 --> 00:21:04,576
Geez, this chair…

280
00:21:06,661 --> 00:21:07,496
Excuse me.

281
00:21:08,413 --> 00:21:11,416
Someone's sitting in Seat One.
Please tell them to switch seats.

282
00:21:11,500 --> 00:21:15,003
-He's sitting there because he booked it.
-It's my seat.

283
00:21:15,087 --> 00:21:17,464
Your one-month reservation
ended yesterday.

284
00:21:17,547 --> 00:21:19,299
But I've always sat there.

285
00:21:19,383 --> 00:21:20,592
You can't do this.

286
00:21:20,675 --> 00:21:22,552
He's retaking the CSAT.

287
00:21:22,636 --> 00:21:24,888
He came this morning
and booked Seat One for a month.

288
00:21:25,972 --> 00:21:28,016
Of all the seats,
why did he have to take mine?

289
00:21:28,100 --> 00:21:31,269
The one who studied there last year
got into Hanguk National University.

290
00:21:31,353 --> 00:21:34,356
So, that seat is popular
among my classmates.

291
00:21:35,232 --> 00:21:38,276
It's near the entrance,
so it's not that good. Try another seat.

292
00:21:38,360 --> 00:21:39,611
Go look around.

293
00:21:47,661 --> 00:21:50,580
It was 8:12 p.m.
That was when I paid with my card.

294
00:21:53,583 --> 00:21:54,418
So?

295
00:21:54,501 --> 00:21:57,587
That's when it would mark one month.

296
00:21:57,671 --> 00:21:58,880
It hasn't passed yet.

297
00:21:59,840 --> 00:22:03,468
You count the bookings by days,
but today's technically not over.

298
00:22:03,552 --> 00:22:04,886
So it means that seat…

299
00:22:06,888 --> 00:22:07,889
is still mine.

300
00:22:10,392 --> 00:22:14,146
Since he's older and retaking the CSAT,

301
00:22:15,147 --> 00:22:17,107
he can have the seat for just today.

302
00:22:17,190 --> 00:22:18,233
I'll allow him that.

303
00:22:24,865 --> 00:22:25,866
Excuse me?

304
00:22:27,325 --> 00:22:28,160
Okay.

305
00:22:28,243 --> 00:22:29,870
I'll talk to him.

306
00:22:31,037 --> 00:22:32,122
Thank you.

307
00:22:33,582 --> 00:22:36,168
I'll book Seat One for a month
starting tomorrow.

308
00:22:36,251 --> 00:22:37,919
-My name is--
-I know.

309
00:22:38,003 --> 00:22:39,754
Im A-sol, the high school senior.

310
00:22:47,179 --> 00:22:48,013
Geez.

311
00:23:10,619 --> 00:23:11,995
Number three is correct. Good job.

312
00:23:12,954 --> 00:23:14,956
For this question, let's look here.

313
00:23:20,754 --> 00:23:21,588
Here.

314
00:23:22,672 --> 00:23:24,758
-This is for you.
-Thank you.

315
00:23:24,841 --> 00:23:27,177
Can you give an extra lesson
this Saturday?

316
00:23:27,928 --> 00:23:30,096
It's finals week. He's free all afternoon.

317
00:23:32,432 --> 00:23:33,683
I can do it in the evening.

318
00:23:34,559 --> 00:23:36,353
He goes to cram school in the evening.

319
00:23:37,646 --> 00:23:39,564
Should I tutor him after that?

320
00:23:40,482 --> 00:23:43,109
That might be too late.
Are you okay with that?

321
00:23:44,569 --> 00:23:45,946
When do I sleep then?

322
00:23:50,408 --> 00:23:52,244
-I'll get going.
-Thanks. Bye.

323
00:23:58,250 --> 00:24:01,503
Tae-seo, how's 2:30 p.m. on Saturday?

324
00:24:01,586 --> 00:24:02,671
Does that work?

325
00:24:07,550 --> 00:24:08,468
Not really.

326
00:24:11,554 --> 00:24:14,432
I may have to work on Saturday morning.

327
00:24:14,516 --> 00:24:17,560
I'm really sorry.
I really need to take this job.

328
00:24:22,565 --> 00:24:23,483
Yes?

329
00:24:23,566 --> 00:24:26,569
I think I can do
an extra lesson on Saturday…

330
00:24:26,653 --> 00:24:27,737
Excuse me. I'm sorry.

331
00:24:29,948 --> 00:24:31,908
HUI-SEO

332
00:24:32,617 --> 00:24:34,369
It was nothing. I can do it.

333
00:24:34,452 --> 00:24:35,704
Thank you so much.

334
00:24:36,246 --> 00:24:37,289
All right, then.

335
00:24:37,372 --> 00:24:40,041
-Okay, good night.
-Good night.

336
00:24:42,002 --> 00:24:44,004
Hey, Hui-seo. I was tutoring.

337
00:24:44,087 --> 00:24:46,089
Tae-seo, you better do well
on your finals.

338
00:24:46,172 --> 00:24:47,674
When you got a B on your midterms,

339
00:24:47,757 --> 00:24:50,302
I was so worried
you'd lose your scholarship.

340
00:24:50,385 --> 00:24:51,386
Okay.

341
00:24:52,595 --> 00:24:55,890
I wasn't going to tell you this,

342
00:24:55,974 --> 00:24:57,767
but Grandma's knees aren't looking good.

343
00:24:59,477 --> 00:25:03,273
They said surgery would fix them,
but she just won't do it.

344
00:25:04,899 --> 00:25:07,360
She has the money for it,
but she won't use it.

345
00:25:07,861 --> 00:25:10,405
She said it's for your tuition
if you lose your scholarship.

346
00:25:11,448 --> 00:25:13,366
So you better ace those exams.

347
00:25:14,743 --> 00:25:17,662
Hey, Grandma is here. I'll call you back.

348
00:26:04,793 --> 00:26:05,627
I'm sorry.

349
00:26:13,009 --> 00:26:15,720
It's okay.
I'll call you after finals are over.

350
00:26:43,581 --> 00:26:44,666
Tae-seo.

351
00:26:47,252 --> 00:26:48,336
Yes?

352
00:26:48,878 --> 00:26:50,547
This question…

353
00:26:51,464 --> 00:26:55,051
It's asking for the equation of a line
with a minimum slope.

354
00:26:55,135 --> 00:26:58,054
You need to find the derivative of F
like I mentioned before.

355
00:27:35,925 --> 00:27:41,181
Is there a place to see flowers near here?
My daughter loves flowers.

356
00:27:42,098 --> 00:27:44,726
When you walk for five minutes
along the path near the beach,

357
00:27:44,809 --> 00:27:45,643
there's a flowerbed.

358
00:27:45,727 --> 00:27:48,271
-Really?
-Thank you.

359
00:27:48,354 --> 00:27:49,647
-Do you like flowers?
-Yeah.

360
00:27:51,566 --> 00:27:52,609
Here. It's for you.

361
00:28:13,463 --> 00:28:15,715
-It's this way.
-Thank you.

362
00:28:23,848 --> 00:28:25,183
It's a gift for you.

363
00:28:27,644 --> 00:28:29,437
Thank you.

364
00:28:32,941 --> 00:28:34,067
Thank you.

365
00:29:18,444 --> 00:29:21,531
Tae-seo. See you at the lab
during vacation.

366
00:29:41,634 --> 00:29:43,344
I'm done with finals. I'm leaving now.

367
00:29:48,600 --> 00:29:50,977
Let's meet up. I'll come to your hotel.

368
00:30:02,780 --> 00:30:04,908
I can see you for only a moment though.

369
00:30:04,991 --> 00:30:07,911
I can't meet outsiders in my uniform.

370
00:30:08,786 --> 00:30:13,333
At 2:30 p.m., I have 30 minutes,
so I'll get changed quickly.

371
00:30:18,922 --> 00:30:22,091
I'm on my way.
There's something on my mind.

372
00:30:22,800 --> 00:30:25,970
The answer is there,
but I have some doubt.

373
00:30:27,055 --> 00:30:30,099
When I see you,
I'm sure it'll become clear.

374
00:30:38,358 --> 00:30:39,484
Eun-a?

375
00:30:40,068 --> 00:30:41,861
You should try this too.

376
00:30:44,072 --> 00:30:45,823
They're making welcome cards
for the suites.

377
00:30:45,907 --> 00:30:47,659
We're trying to come up
with new greetings.

378
00:30:49,327 --> 00:30:50,578
Are drawings okay too?

379
00:30:51,204 --> 00:30:52,121
What kind of drawings?

380
00:31:13,893 --> 00:31:15,103
Something like this.

381
00:31:15,895 --> 00:31:17,146
Give it a try.

382
00:31:17,230 --> 00:31:20,483
If it gets selected, it'll be served
with the welcome food for a month.

383
00:31:25,905 --> 00:31:28,282
Can I come back in 30 minutes?

384
00:31:28,366 --> 00:31:30,785
Do you want me to wait for 30 minutes?

385
00:31:30,868 --> 00:31:33,204
You drew that in a minute.
Why don't you do it now?

386
00:31:35,748 --> 00:31:37,417
I need to be somewhere for a moment.

387
00:32:11,117 --> 00:32:12,118
It's been a while.

388
00:32:12,910 --> 00:32:14,537
It feels like it's been years.

389
00:32:21,836 --> 00:32:24,338
I couldn't get changed. Sorry.

390
00:32:38,561 --> 00:32:42,440
I'll be home during the break,
so let's see each other more often.

391
00:32:43,232 --> 00:32:44,233
Ms. Mo Eun-a.

392
00:32:53,701 --> 00:32:56,204
Excuse me. Where was the exit?

393
00:32:56,287 --> 00:32:58,289
You can go around this way to exit.

394
00:32:59,457 --> 00:33:00,458
Thank you.

395
00:33:38,329 --> 00:33:39,872
Was he the guy?

396
00:33:45,795 --> 00:33:47,505
Ms. Mo Eun-a, you can't go out in uniform…

397
00:33:52,844 --> 00:33:53,845
Tae-seo!

398
00:34:00,143 --> 00:34:01,435
I'm sorry!

399
00:34:26,460 --> 00:34:28,629
You always have the right answer

400
00:34:30,089 --> 00:34:32,425
because you don't jump to conclusions.

401
00:34:33,301 --> 00:34:35,511
You don't do anything
just for the sake of it.

402
00:34:51,277 --> 00:34:52,987
You came back exactly in 30 minutes.

403
00:34:55,907 --> 00:35:00,786
Here. I liked your corn drawing.

404
00:35:02,788 --> 00:35:04,248
I'll draw it now.

405
00:35:12,048 --> 00:35:15,718
Your resume said you majored
in early childhood education.

406
00:35:16,344 --> 00:35:18,804
I guess that's why
the way you treat people is different.

407
00:35:19,639 --> 00:35:23,100
How should I say it?
You're filled with affection.

408
00:35:24,477 --> 00:35:25,478
I am?

409
00:35:27,563 --> 00:35:28,689
Thank you.

410
00:35:59,720 --> 00:36:00,805
Sir.

411
00:36:01,681 --> 00:36:02,932
I'm getting off.

412
00:36:04,183 --> 00:36:05,184
Sir!

413
00:36:24,287 --> 00:36:25,288
Aren't you getting off?

414
00:36:27,790 --> 00:36:29,583
No, it's fine.

415
00:36:45,182 --> 00:36:46,851
Get a job after graduating?

416
00:36:49,520 --> 00:36:53,190
Honestly, studying for four years
has already been a luxury for me.

417
00:36:56,485 --> 00:36:57,486
I see.

418
00:36:58,904 --> 00:37:02,908
You want what you have to do,
not what you like to do.

419
00:37:06,287 --> 00:37:08,873
That's strong. It resonates with me.

420
00:37:14,253 --> 00:37:16,881
You sure you won't regret it?
I'm already sad.

421
00:37:17,757 --> 00:37:19,050
I'm not the type to look back.

422
00:37:26,599 --> 00:37:29,393
Can I wrap things up
and close the lab today?

423
00:38:20,778 --> 00:38:26,534
JULY

424
00:38:30,746 --> 00:38:33,499
Interns can move into the residence hall.

425
00:38:33,582 --> 00:38:36,210
Why wait? I'm going to move in right away.

426
00:38:38,546 --> 00:38:40,214
So you're going to live there then?

427
00:38:40,297 --> 00:38:43,634
If you have a big bag like a suitcase,
could you lend it to me?

428
00:38:43,717 --> 00:38:45,636
I've never traveled before.

429
00:38:45,719 --> 00:38:46,554
I need to pack.

430
00:38:47,680 --> 00:38:50,516
-You can use mine.
-Would that be okay?

431
00:38:53,227 --> 00:38:55,980
So what will it be, Eun-a?

432
00:38:56,063 --> 00:38:57,565
Want to borrow my suitcase?

433
00:38:58,065 --> 00:38:59,900
Tell me
since you're the one who'll use it.

434
00:39:00,609 --> 00:39:01,777
Could I borrow it?

435
00:39:01,861 --> 00:39:04,405
Silver, black, white, or yellow?

436
00:39:04,488 --> 00:39:05,489
Which one?

437
00:39:06,365 --> 00:39:07,575
The biggest one.

438
00:39:07,658 --> 00:39:11,203
The biggest one. Okay.

439
00:40:15,226 --> 00:40:18,229
I would've prepared a better breakfast
if you had told me earlier.

440
00:40:19,480 --> 00:40:21,065
I actually wanted pine nut porridge.

441
00:40:25,736 --> 00:40:29,031
-What about your wedding?
-What wedding?

442
00:40:29,114 --> 00:40:30,783
What? You made a big fuss about it.

443
00:40:32,993 --> 00:40:34,328
We'll live together first.

444
00:40:34,995 --> 00:40:36,622
She might run away.

445
00:40:36,705 --> 00:40:38,499
If she does,
I should make it easy for her.

446
00:40:40,209 --> 00:40:42,586
I don't understand grown-ups.

447
00:40:47,841 --> 00:40:50,302
What? You don't like that I'm leaving?

448
00:40:53,931 --> 00:40:55,391
When did you grow up so fast?

449
00:40:56,517 --> 00:40:57,851
I've done nothing for you.

450
00:40:59,812 --> 00:41:01,355
You gave me a lot of love.

451
00:41:03,065 --> 00:41:05,526
Yes, I did that more than anyone.

452
00:41:06,318 --> 00:41:07,903
You regained your health,

453
00:41:08,862 --> 00:41:11,615
so I decided to go to college
in the summer of my senior year.

454
00:41:11,699 --> 00:41:14,952
When college wasn't my thing,
I found another path.

455
00:41:15,035 --> 00:41:16,662
It's all thanks to you.

456
00:41:24,920 --> 00:41:25,963
I'll…

457
00:41:26,630 --> 00:41:28,507
I'll be all right,

458
00:41:29,592 --> 00:41:31,010
so go enjoy your life.

459
00:41:32,386 --> 00:41:33,637
Live as if you're on a journey.

460
00:41:36,307 --> 00:41:37,683
Just do all the things you want.

461
00:41:42,938 --> 00:41:43,939
I'll do that.

462
00:41:46,233 --> 00:41:48,944
You know I'll never waste
the time you've given me.

463
00:41:58,787 --> 00:42:00,998
-Does it taste good?
-Dad, you're the best.

464
00:42:16,305 --> 00:42:17,806
YEONWOO HIGH SCHOOL
YEON TAE-SEO

465
00:42:39,370 --> 00:42:43,165
I didn't tell your dad about that boy.

466
00:42:43,248 --> 00:42:46,293
You can tell him. He knows we're close.

467
00:42:50,589 --> 00:42:53,467
Seong-chan told me
you're good at your work.

468
00:43:03,769 --> 00:43:06,980
Don't ever leave Dad by himself.

469
00:43:07,606 --> 00:43:08,816
Even if he's healthy now,

470
00:43:11,151 --> 00:43:12,152
don't ever do it.

471
00:43:14,613 --> 00:43:15,739
I'll stick close to him.

472
00:43:21,870 --> 00:43:26,500
ROOM 407

473
00:43:26,583 --> 00:43:28,836
JEONG JAE-WON
MO EUN-A

474
00:44:11,295 --> 00:44:12,713
YEONWOO HIGH SCHOOL
YEON TAE-SEO

475
00:44:35,736 --> 00:44:38,363
It's a job posting
for an overseas internship next year.

476
00:44:38,447 --> 00:44:42,159
You'll have a good shot at it
once you build your career here.

477
00:44:42,242 --> 00:44:43,911
Just study English in your spare time.

478
00:44:44,912 --> 00:44:47,790
I hope this will help you
stand on your own.

479
00:44:56,673 --> 00:45:00,761
CAFETERIA HOURS DURING SUMMER VACATION

480
00:45:20,072 --> 00:45:23,492
I'll get home at 2:00 p.m.
When do you want to meet?

481
00:45:33,919 --> 00:45:35,921
Grandpa, the light will work fine now.

482
00:45:36,588 --> 00:45:37,673
Okay.

483
00:45:41,218 --> 00:45:43,220
Grandma should see a doctor.

484
00:45:44,221 --> 00:45:47,057
She won't.
There's no point in telling her.

485
00:45:48,392 --> 00:45:51,979
I'll make an appointment.
You should take her.

486
00:45:55,440 --> 00:45:59,820
Geez. I worry the roof will collapse
during the monsoon.

487
00:45:59,903 --> 00:46:01,655
All the firewood will get wet.

488
00:46:01,738 --> 00:46:05,284
I get paid monthly
for renting out the storage.

489
00:46:06,201 --> 00:46:08,287
It's only a few tens of thousands of won,

490
00:46:08,370 --> 00:46:11,373
but I have to make sure
this gets passed on to Hui-seo later.

491
00:46:15,669 --> 00:46:17,796
I'll take that to mean
she'll go to the hospital.

492
00:46:22,968 --> 00:46:29,600
YEONWOO WOODWORKING STUDIO

493
00:46:31,310 --> 00:46:32,644
-Hello.
-Hey.

494
00:46:36,481 --> 00:46:37,899
What brings you here, Tae-seo?

495
00:46:37,983 --> 00:46:39,568
I'm on break, so I'm visiting.

496
00:46:39,651 --> 00:46:43,155
Grandpa's worried
the wood will get wet during the monsoon.

497
00:46:43,238 --> 00:46:44,489
He wants something to cover it.

498
00:46:45,032 --> 00:46:47,409
That roof looks like it would leak,
but it never does.

499
00:46:47,492 --> 00:46:51,079
But I'll get you something tomorrow
that will cover the whole thing.

500
00:46:51,163 --> 00:46:52,331
Thank you.

501
00:46:52,414 --> 00:46:54,708
I don't think it'll leak either.

502
00:46:54,791 --> 00:46:58,128
But I guess he's so worried
he can't even sleep.

503
00:46:58,795 --> 00:47:00,047
That's not it.

504
00:47:00,130 --> 00:47:03,050
Anyway, you should hurry
and get your military service done.

505
00:47:03,133 --> 00:47:04,926
That's all he talks about when he's drunk.

506
00:47:05,010 --> 00:47:07,846
If something happens to them
when you're in the military,

507
00:47:07,929 --> 00:47:10,015
he's so worried Hui-seo will be all alone.

508
00:47:11,558 --> 00:47:15,062
You can enlist early these days.
Hurry and get it over with.

509
00:47:43,465 --> 00:47:50,430
I'LL GET HOME AT 2:00 P.M.
WHEN DO YOU WANT TO MEET?

510
00:47:57,938 --> 00:47:59,022
It's so hot.

511
00:48:00,357 --> 00:48:01,942
Staying at the hotel would be better.

512
00:48:03,777 --> 00:48:05,487
The schedule changes all the time.

513
00:48:07,614 --> 00:48:08,824
We're always on standby.

514
00:48:11,118 --> 00:48:12,744
Can you believe the AC's broken?

515
00:48:14,996 --> 00:48:17,916
Aren't you hot, Eun-a?
Should I make the fan turn?

516
00:48:17,999 --> 00:48:19,626
No, they'll fly away.

517
00:48:21,962 --> 00:48:24,172
You're still working on the welcome cards?

518
00:48:26,758 --> 00:48:29,136
I'm making them
with the writing and drawing this time.

519
00:48:29,219 --> 00:48:30,429
The writing is the hard part.

520
00:48:31,430 --> 00:48:33,640
I wasn't selected
when I only did the drawings.

521
00:48:37,185 --> 00:48:38,186
I'll get it this time.

522
00:48:39,730 --> 00:48:41,815
WELCOME TO OUR HOTEL
WHERE YOU CAN SEE THE OCEAN

523
00:48:41,898 --> 00:48:44,192
ENJOY THE LAID-BACK VIBE
OF GANGWON AT OUR HOTEL

524
00:48:47,279 --> 00:48:48,780
"Welcome…"

525
00:49:03,879 --> 00:49:10,635
I'LL GET HOME AT 2:00 P.M.
WHEN DO YOU WANT TO MEET?

526
00:49:25,066 --> 00:49:27,652
I'm home. When do you get off work?

527
00:49:30,655 --> 00:49:32,240
I'm in the dorms.

528
00:49:33,909 --> 00:49:34,743
I see.

529
00:49:35,994 --> 00:49:36,912
You moved in.

530
00:49:37,662 --> 00:49:38,872
I was going to tell you,

531
00:49:39,581 --> 00:49:41,416
but I moved in
as soon as I became an intern,

532
00:49:41,500 --> 00:49:42,876
so it was hectic.

533
00:49:46,171 --> 00:49:47,214
Right.

534
00:49:51,092 --> 00:49:53,845
Do you have time? I'll come over.

535
00:49:54,513 --> 00:49:55,639
It's a quick bus ride.

536
00:49:58,809 --> 00:50:02,604
If now isn't a good time,
I can see you in the evening.

537
00:50:03,146 --> 00:50:04,731
Today, I…

538
00:50:16,660 --> 00:50:17,786
Don't come, Tae-seo.

539
00:50:20,497 --> 00:50:22,707
I mean today. Don't come today.

540
00:50:25,752 --> 00:50:28,922
-I'll be there tomorrow.
-No, not tomorrow either.

541
00:50:33,593 --> 00:50:35,011
When are you coming home?

542
00:50:36,096 --> 00:50:39,349
I can't. Like I said, I live here now.

543
00:50:43,144 --> 00:50:45,564
Tae-seo, the thing is…

544
00:50:47,899 --> 00:50:51,027
I'm going back to Seoul
the day after tomorrow to tutor.

545
00:50:51,111 --> 00:50:53,321
Let's try to work out our schedules again.

546
00:51:00,954 --> 00:51:02,581
Don't.

547
00:51:04,833 --> 00:51:08,628
Let's stop forcing our schedules to match.

548
00:51:09,671 --> 00:51:12,007
This time is so precious to lose for me.

549
00:51:12,632 --> 00:51:14,759
I want to make use of it all.

550
00:51:17,178 --> 00:51:21,892
I've found something I want to do,
and it matters a lot to me.

551
00:51:22,475 --> 00:51:25,395
I just need to do it.
I really want to excel at it.

552
00:51:26,062 --> 00:51:28,565
You should stop wasting time
going back and forth.

553
00:51:28,648 --> 00:51:30,150
Spend the time on yourself.

554
00:51:30,859 --> 00:51:33,320
Let's not waste
a single moment of our time.

555
00:51:43,496 --> 00:51:44,497
Well…

556
00:51:45,999 --> 00:51:47,292
I mean…

557
00:51:48,084 --> 00:51:49,628
I don't know what you're saying…

558
00:51:53,715 --> 00:51:55,008
But why can I understand it?

559
00:52:00,388 --> 00:52:02,265
Why do I get it all?

560
00:52:17,989 --> 00:52:19,032
Okay.

561
00:52:27,707 --> 00:52:28,750
Let's do that.

562
00:52:45,725 --> 00:52:46,726
That's what we'll do.

563
00:54:12,604 --> 00:54:14,189
This vegetable drawing is so cute.

564
00:54:14,272 --> 00:54:16,775
Yes. The corn is so adorable.

565
00:54:18,276 --> 00:54:20,153
Did you draw this, Eun-a?

566
00:54:21,654 --> 00:54:22,655
Yes.

567
00:54:23,406 --> 00:54:26,576
I think the writing fits
our hotel's image better too.

568
00:54:51,893 --> 00:54:55,688
You like people, you're good at English,
and you draw vegetables well.

569
00:54:56,356 --> 00:54:58,817
I know there's a job out there
you can give your all to.

570
00:55:00,068 --> 00:55:01,194
It'll work out

571
00:55:02,987 --> 00:55:04,864
in ways we never imagined.

572
00:55:07,575 --> 00:55:11,079
We'll know for sure what that is
once we become adults.

573
00:55:13,623 --> 00:55:14,624
You were right.

574
00:55:16,459 --> 00:55:18,128
In ways we never imagined,

575
00:55:19,921 --> 00:55:20,922
we…

576
00:56:45,506 --> 00:56:52,472
DECEMBER

577
00:57:10,365 --> 00:57:11,199
Goodness.

578
00:57:11,991 --> 00:57:14,494
Is it because the weather's cold?

579
00:57:15,411 --> 00:57:18,873
No one's picking up
because it's too early in the day.

580
00:57:18,957 --> 00:57:20,041
What do we do?

581
00:57:20,124 --> 00:57:22,168
We need help.

582
00:57:22,252 --> 00:57:25,547
-It's okay. I can ride the bus.
-Aren't you going to be late?

583
00:57:25,630 --> 00:57:28,049
And you need to shave your head
before going to boot camp.

584
00:57:28,132 --> 00:57:29,509
-I'll make it if I go now.
-What?

585
00:57:29,592 --> 00:57:31,427
-I'll get going. Don't come.
-Gosh. Oh, no.

586
00:57:31,511 --> 00:57:32,345
Goodness.

587
00:57:32,428 --> 00:57:33,805
-I'll go.
-You can't go like this.

588
00:57:34,764 --> 00:57:35,598
Hey.

589
00:57:37,058 --> 00:57:38,518
-Goodness, are you all right?
-Gosh.

590
00:57:38,601 --> 00:57:41,980
-Gosh, dear!
-Tae-seo. What about him?

591
00:57:53,491 --> 00:57:54,951
Go back. It's slippery.

592
00:57:55,994 --> 00:57:57,161
Just go then.

593
00:58:00,873 --> 00:58:01,708
Don't get hurt.

594
00:58:04,460 --> 00:58:05,461
Don't you dare get hurt.

595
00:58:09,048 --> 00:58:10,174
I'll get going.

596
00:58:43,041 --> 00:58:45,001
I used to hate
thinking about the next step.

597
00:58:46,419 --> 00:58:48,338
But I started to think about the future

598
00:58:49,797 --> 00:58:51,382
because of what you would always say.

599
00:58:54,010 --> 00:58:57,138
Where we'll be, what we'll do,
and with who…

600
00:59:03,561 --> 00:59:05,647
It made me curious about my future.

601
00:59:07,065 --> 00:59:08,524
About myself.

602
00:59:10,818 --> 00:59:13,946
About what I wanted and what I could do.

603
00:59:18,451 --> 00:59:22,163
The countless worries about the future
began with you.

604
00:59:24,248 --> 00:59:26,668
And they ended
with the expressions on your face,

605
00:59:27,418 --> 00:59:30,838
your responses, and your answers.

606
00:59:32,256 --> 00:59:33,591
I realize that now.

607
00:59:39,639 --> 00:59:43,643
Without you, I lose interest in myself.

608
00:59:52,860 --> 00:59:56,656
I have no curiosity about myself.

609
00:59:58,991 --> 01:00:03,454
That makes me scared and sad.

610
01:00:07,417 --> 01:00:10,169
Where we'll be, what we'll do…

611
01:00:13,172 --> 01:00:14,173
and with who…

612
01:00:18,886 --> 01:00:25,852
SEPTEMBER, 10 YEARS LATER

613
01:01:13,232 --> 01:01:15,526
The train will depart now.
The doors are closing.

614
01:01:28,247 --> 01:01:30,374
Doors closed. Screen doors closed.

615
01:01:30,458 --> 01:01:31,834
Train departing.

616
01:01:55,525 --> 01:01:59,028
STILL SHINING

617
01:02:28,516 --> 01:02:30,518
Subtitle translation by: Hye Won Yoon
